d Kingdom","England":"England","Nantwich, Cheshire, England":"Nantwich, Cheshire, England"},"nl":{"1140–1219":"1140–1219","1138–Male":"1138–Overleden","1140–1190":"1140–1190","1166–1233":"1166–1233","1142–1219":"1142–1219","1170–1220":"1170–1220","1117–1167":"1117–1167","1120–1144":"1120–1144","1190":"1190","about 1170":"circa 1170","1220":"1220","1120":"1120","1142":"1142","1140":"1140","1170":"1170","1117":"1117","1215":"1215","1138":"1138","1159":"van 8 januari 1159 to 7 januari 1160","1167":"1167","1233":"1233","1144":"1144","1166":"1166","about 1132":"circa 1132","after 1167":"na 1167","1219":"1219","Barthomley, Cheshire, England":"Barthomley, Cheshire, England","Sible Hedingham, Essex, England":"Sible Hedingham, Essex, England","Chester, Cheshire, England":"Blacon, Chester, Cheshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","England":"England","Nantwich, Cheshire, England":"Nantwich, Cheshire, England"},"en":{"1140–1219":"1140–1219","1138–Male":"1138–Deceased","1140–1190":"1140–1190","1166–1233":"1166–1233","1142–1219":"1142–1219","1170–1220":"1170–1220","1117–1167":"1117–1167","1120–1144":"1120–1144","1190":"1190","about 1170":"about 1170","1220":"1220","1120":"1120","1142":"1142","1140":"1140","1170":"1170","1117":"1117","1215":"1215","1138":"1138","1159":"from 8 January 1159 to 7 January 1160","1167":"1167","1233":"1233","1144":"1144","1166":"1166","about 1132":"about 1132","after 1167":"after 1167","1219":"1219","Barthomley, Cheshire, England":"Barthomley, Cheshire, England","Sible Hedingham, Essex, England":"Sible Hedingham, Essex, England","Chester, Cheshire, England":"Blacon, Chester, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England","Nantwich, Cheshire, England":"Nantwich, Cheshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]},{"name":"of","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Oswald   or any of the various other names beginning with <i>Os-</i>."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":75,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When William of Barthomley de Praers was born in 1140, in Nantwich, Cheshire, England, his father, Richard de Praers II, was 23 and his mother, Mrs. Galtha e Praers, was 20. He married Elizabeth de Prethorn from 8 January 1159 to 7 January 1160, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1219, in his hometown, at the age of 79."},"et":{"1140–1219":"1140–1219","1138–Male":"1138–Surnud","1140–1190":"1140–1190","1166–1233":"1166–1233","1142–1219":"1142–1219","1170–1220":"1170–1220","1117–1167":"1117–1167","1120–1144":"1120–1144","1190":"1190","about 1170":"umbes 1170","1220":"1220","1120":"1120","1142":"1142","1140":"1140","1170":"1170","1117":"1117","1215":"1215","1138":"1138","1159":"8. jaanuar 1159 kuni 7. jaanuar 1160","1167":"1167","1233":"1233","1144":"1144","1166":"1166","about 1132":"umbes 1132","after 1167":"pärast 1167","1219":"1219","Barthomley, Cheshire, England":"Barthomley, Cheshire, England","Sible Hedingham, Essex, England":"Sible Hedingham, Essex, England","Chester, Cheshire, England":"Blacon, Chester, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Nantwich, Cheshire, England":"Nantwich, Cheshire, England"},"fi":{"1140–1219":"1140–1219","1138–Male":"1138–Kuollut","1140–1190":"1140–1190","1166–1233":"1166–1233","1142–1219":"1142–1219","1170–1220":"1170–1220","1117–1167":"1117–1167","1120–1144":"1120–1144","1190":"1190","about 1170":"noin 1170","1220":"1220","1120":"1120","1142":"1142","1140":"1140","1170":"1170","1117":"1117","1215":"1215","1138":"1138","1159":"vuodesta 8. tammikuuta 1159 vuoteen 7. tammikuuta 1160","1167":"1167","1233":"1233","1144":"1144","1166":"1166","about 1132":"noin 1132","after 1167":"1167 jälkeen","1219":"1219","Barthomley, Cheshire, England":"Barthomley, Cheshire, England","Sible Hedingham, Essex, England":"Sible Hedingham, Essex, England","Chester, Cheshire, England":"Blacon, Chester, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":